Date: Wed 30 May 2012
Source: ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) [edited]
http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-05-30/two-new-hendra-virus-cases-reported-in-qld/4041668/?site=northqldÂ§ion=news


Biosecurity authorities have confirmed 2 horses have died in separate outbreaks of hendra virus in central and north Queensland. The properties near Rockhampton and at Ingham have been quarantined. Queensland Health staff are on their way to the 2 properties where it is understood a total of 4 people have had exposure to the sick horses.

In 2009, there was an outbreak at a Cawarral property near Rockhampton, where local vet Alistair Rodgers and several horses died. Last year [2011], hendra virus was detected at Hervey Bay, in northern Brisbane, and also on the Gold Coast.

A property south of Townsville was placed under quarantine after another outbreak in January [2012].

[Byline: Marlina Whop]

